==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Coax
<hw>Coax</hw> <pr>(k⟦omac⟧ks; 110)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Coaxed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>;
<pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Coaxing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf.
OE. <ets>cokes</ets> fool, a person easily imposed upon, W.
<ets>coeg</ets> empty, foolish; F. <ets>coquin</ets> knave,
rogue.]</ety> <def>To persuade by gentle, insinuating courtesy,
flattering, or fondling; to wheedle; to soothe.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To wheedle; cajole; flatter; persuade;
entice.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coax</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
